'''JWM''' ('''J'''oe's '''W'''indow '''M'''anager) is [[Article description::an extremely lightweight [[window manager]] for the [[X]] window system.]] Its installed size is less than 1.15 MB, regardless of the enabled USE flags. 

== Installation ==

=== USE flags ===

{{USEflag|package=x11-wm/jwm}}

=== Emerge ===

{{Emerge|x11-wm/jwm}}

== Configuration ==

=== Files ===

Configuration files are in XML format.

* {{Path|/etc/system.jwmrc}} - Global (system wide) configuration file.
* {{Path|~/.jwmrc}} - Local (per user) configuration file.

Additional information on configuring JWM can be found in the {{Path|/usr/share/doc/jwm-2.3.6/}} directory.

== Usage ==

=== Invocation ===

{{Invocation|jwm -h|output=
JWM v2.3.6 by Joe Wingbermuehle
compiled options: confirm icons jpeg nls png shape svg xbm xft xinerama xrender 
system configuration: /etc/system.jwmrc
usage: jwm [ options ]
  -display X  Set the X display to use
  -exit       Exit JWM (send _JWM_EXIT to the root)
  -f file     Use specified configuration file
  -h          Display this help message
  -p          Parse the configuration file and exit
  -reload     Reload menu (send _JWM_RELOAD to the root)
  -restart    Restart JWM (send _JWM_RESTART to the root)
  -v          Display version information
}}

